14.08||||Everyone knows that cats are the most illogical and unpredictable pets. Can you work out what's going through that furry little head?  
28.12||||However, cats have their language. And if you learn it, there's a chance you'll understand them much better.  
34.08||||We've put together all the possible cat behaviors to help you find a common language with your pet.  
40.06||||Well, if it allows you to.  
42.6||||Also, we've prepared three essential tips that will help you communicate with cats better.  
51.14||||One - the tail is raised.  
55.58||||A raised upward and curled tail means your cat is happy with its life.  
60.44||||Congrats. You are already best friends with your cat. How did you manage to do it, by the way?  
66.229||||Do you know any secrets on how to please cats? Let us know in the comments below, so that others can learn your tricks, too.  
76.12||||Occasional twitches.  
77.66||||Occasional twitches means your cat is excited or worried about something.  
81.89||||Also, vets say when a cat nervously jerks its tail or keeps knocking its tail on the floor, it means your pet is in  
89.74||||pain or stressed. Maybe it's time to take your cat to a vet.  
96.08||||The fur juts out. When the fur on the cat's tail juts out in different directions,  
101.2||||it means your fluffy friend is very excited, or feels threatened.  
105.68||||The aim of fluffing the tail is to create an illusion that the cat is larger than it is.  
110.92||||That way, your cat is showing its enemy that it's really big and scary to deal with.  
117.89||||The tail vibrates. The cat vibrates its tail slightly when it's agitated and glad to see you.  
124.67||||It also means that your cat is excited waiting for something, for instance, for a treat.  
132.96||||The tail sticks straight up.  
135.05||||If your cat sticks its tail straight up and bends its back to form an "N", you need to pay special attention to this.  
142.74||||It's a sign of extreme aggression, and it occurs during self-defense. If nothing dangerous happens around,  
150.0||||try to calm your cat down by petting it.  
154.68||||The tail is inclined at a low angle. The straight, but inclined tail is a sign of slight aggression or fright.  
162.63||||Also, when a cat doesn't know if there is a friend or enemy around, it keeps the tail at an angle of 45 degrees.  
172.5||||The tail is lowered. The cat lowers its tail toward the ground when it's frightened or feels guilty.  
179.66||||Most often, cats tuck their tails between their paws when they're afraid of something or someone.  
185.37||||Also, it's a sign of insecurity and submission. Have a look around the house. Your cat has probably done something naughty,  
193.08||||and lowers its tail knowing that you're going to punish it.  
198.209||||The tail is wagging from side to side. If your cat wags his tail sharply from side to side, it means it is angry.  
205.53||||It's best to leave your pet alone. However, it might also mean that you cat wants to play with you.  
212.45||||Why do cats wag their tails while sitting next to their owners and feeling completely satisfied?  
218.069||||It's simple. The cat checks if there's an enemy behind its back.  
224.849||||Two - the eyes. Dilated pupils.  
231.0||||Dilated pupils indicates strong feelings: playfulness,  
234.72||||agitation, fright, or aggression. In case a house is new for your cat,  
240.06||||it dilates its pupils as a sign that it's not used to the new place yet. Your cat needs time to examine the situation  
247.14||||and people around.  
251.24||||A direct look. When a cat looks directly in your eyes, it means it trusts you. Your pet is comfortable being around you.  
262.14||||A slow blink. A slow blink indicates that your cat is calm. Your pet feels comfortable and safe.  
268.919||||Sometimes, it might even purr while blinking slowly.  
277.05||||Three - interactions with people.  
281.16||||Rubbing against you. If a cat rubs against you, it is marking you as its territory and property.  
290.189||||Poking. Poking with a wet nose is an expression of attachment. It indicates your cat feels comfortable and safe being around you.  
302.789||||Rubbing his head or tail. When the cat rubs its head, side, or tail against you, it is just saying hello.  
313.319||||Butting slightly. Butting you slightly with its head is a sign of friendliness. Your pet is in love with you.  
323.999||||Shifting from one paw to another. Cats often move from one paw to another when they are happy or want to play.  
334.14||||Licking you. If a cat licks you, it's a definite sign that it trusts you and considers you part of its family.  
344.12||||Eating your hair. When your cat bites your hair, it's simply trying to clean you. It is another strong sign of love and trust.  
357.36||||Biting you. When a cat bites you, take it as a sign that your pet wants to be left alone. Yep.  
363.42||||Cats also need to have some private time, as well as us humans. On the other hand, light biting means your cat is just playing with you.  
374.14||||Four - other gestures.  
378.2||||If a cat raises its nose up and throws its head,  
381.22||||it's saying, "I see you." Cats often make this gesture to people walking past the window. Have you ever noticed it?  
392.3||||A cat might press its ears against its head if it feels scared, worried, or wants to play.  
398.06||||They also do this when they are sniffing something that's interested them.  
405.94||||When a cat sticks its tongue out slightly and licks itself, it's worried or anxious.  
416.14||||Five - cat language. Cats generally greet people or announce their presence with a short sound.  
426.889||||Lengthy meowing indicates that your cat is very glad to see you. This occurs if you're away from home for a long time.  
437.509||||A medium-length meow might be a request for water or food.  
444.8||||A long sound (a mix of purring and meowing) is a more insistent request or demand.  
454.26||||A low meow is a complaint or indication of dissatisfaction. Also, it might mean your cat is ready to fight.  
463.62||||A loud sound often indicates an urgent demand (for instance, your cat needs more food).  
472.08||||A purring or vibrating sound indicates a desire for closer contact or attention. Cats purr for various reasons,  
479.27||||but most often they do it when they are happy.  
